# BASELINE REPRODUCTION: Mutate Chained Renames
# Validates how the parser handles multiple rename operations in the same block.
# In logstash, operations in the same `mutate` block are processed in a specific
# internal order, but sequential renames often have surprising lineage.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: The parser MUST correctly track the lineage and final field
# names, handling the sequential renaming without losing the source token.
filter {
  mutate {
    rename => { 
      "field_a" => "field_b" 
      "field_b" => "field_c" 
    }
  }
}
